  "prompt": "What are some of the funniest movies you've ever seen?",
  "response": "Humor is subjective, but here are some movies that many people find hilarious:\n\n1. **Airplane! (1980)** - A classic parody film full of absurd humor and witty one-liners.\n2. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail (1975)** - British comedy at its finest with surreal and satirical takes on the legend of King Arthur.\n3. **Groundhog Day (1993)** - Bill Murray shines in this clever and comedic tale of a man stuck in a time loop.\n4. **Superbad (2007)** - A coming-of-age comedy with memorable performances and plenty of laughs.\n5. **Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy (2004)** - Will Ferrell stars in this over-the-top satire of 1970s news culture.\n6. **The Hangover (2009)** - A wild and outrageous story of a bachelor party gone wrong.\n7. **Bridesmaids (2011)** - A hilarious take on wedding preparations and friendship, with standout performances from Kristen Wiig and Melissa McCarthy.\n8. **Step Brothers (2008)** - Will Ferrell and John C. Reilly play two immature adults forced to live together as stepbrothers.\n9. **Dumb and Dumber (1994)** - Jim Carrey and Jeff Daniels deliver slapstick humor in this tale of two clueless friends.\n10. **Hot Fuzz (2007)** - A clever and funny action-comedy from the creators of Shaun of the Dead.\n\nThese films are known for their humor and have been enjoyed by many, but individual tastes will vary.",
